<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1913-03-01T10:40:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1913-03-01T10:40:00-05:00" n="898" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d898">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/6443.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Consul at Nuevo
                                    Laredo</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Nuevo Laredo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-03-01T09:00:00-06:40">
                                    <hi rend="italic">March 1, 1913—9 a.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Peace commission held harmonious session here yesterday and departed this
                            morning for El Paso via San Antonio. In addition to those named in my
                            February 27, 2 [5] p.m., the following personnel are included in the
                            party: Pasqual Orozco, sr., Andres Garze Galan, Cristoforo Caballero,
                            José Cordova, Rafael R. Flores, Nicanor Valdez, Indalecio Vara, Juan
                            Garza Galan, and Adolfo Fuentes.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Garrett</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>